tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly decreased HbA1c and fasting glucose, suggesting possible hypoglycemia or tight glycemic control. Creatinine is slightly low, which may reflect reduced muscle mass in the elderly. Total CO₂ is mildly decreased, possibly indicating mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation is recommended.
